Server Creation = nodejs+express
--------------------------------

Basic commands
--------------

1)Creation of the package.json - npm init
2)Creation of the node modules - npm i express (Installing of express)
3)Install mongoose-npm i mongoose

Basic Steps
-----------

1)Creating a folder(Bank server)
2)Create package.json
3)Install express
4)Create index.js
5)Import express inside the index.js
6)Create an app using the express
7)Setup port number
8)Resolving http request
    Get-To get the data
    post-To post the data
    put- update data partially
    patch-update data completely.
    delete-to delete the data completely.
9)HTTP response code
   1xx-Information
   2xx-Succesfull
   3xx-Redirection
   4xx-Client error
   5xx-Server error
10)JWT Token
    Install JWT-npm i jsonwebtoken
    TO generate a token-sign()

11)Middleware
    It comes in the middle of the request and response cycle of the nodejs execution process
      1)Application specific middleware -for the entire application
      req,res,next
      2)Router specific middleware-for particular part of the application. -validate token-verify() -jsonwebtoken
12)database integration
   1)Install mongoose-npm i mongoose
13)Asynchronous function resolving-promise
  1)Resolve State - .then()
  2)Reject state - catch()
14)CORS - Cross origin resource sharing
   install cors-npm i cors

   port 4200(angular)------request----->3000(nodejs)(recieve)
15)Asynchronous call-RxJs - (Reactive extension for java script)

  Js-Promise
  Ts-RxJs(library)

     1)Observable - 
        a)resolved - Subscribe()
        b)reject - catch